  • Classes in com.fuzzylimes.jsr.resources used by com.fuzzylimes.jsr.clients 
    Class and Description
    BulkGame
    Representation of a Game returned in a Bulk request
    Category 
    Developer
    Developers are the persons and/of studios responsible for developing games, for example Acclaim Entertainment, Bethesda Softworks, Edmund McMillen etc.
    Engine
    Engines are software frameworks used in the creation of games, for example the DOOM engine, Unreal Engine, Geo-Mod etc.
    Game
    Games are the thing that runs are being done against.
    GameType
    Game types are classifications for unofficial games, for example ROM Hack, Fangame, Modification etc.
    Genre
    Genres are classifications for games, for example Action, JRPG, Rogue-like etc.
    Guest
    Sometimes, speedrun.com has runs done by players that have no account on the site yet.
    Leaderboard 
    Level
    Levels are the stages/worlds/maps within a game.
    PagedResponse
    Handles the deserialization of paginated responses.
    PersonalBest
    A user's personal best for a given run
    Platform
    Platforms are hardware devices that run games, for example PC, NES, PS2 etc.
    Publisher
    Publishers are companies that publish games, for example Capcom, SEGA, Midway Games etc.
    Region
    Regions represent the different distribution zones in which games are published, for example the US, Europe or Japan.
    Run
    Runs are the records that represent completed speed run attempts for a given game.
    Series 
    User
    Users are the individuals who have registered an account on speedrun.com.
    Variable
    Variables are custom criteria to distinguish between runs done in the same category or level.
